          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/29952.Jean_Genet"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1605227116p3/29952.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/29952.Jean_Genet">Jean Genet
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
916
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer14057172998271617008">Jean Genet (1910-1986), poet, novelist, playwright, and political essayist, was one of the most significant French writers of the twentieth century. His work, much of it considered scandalous when it first appeared, is now placed among the classics of modern literature and has been translated and performed throughout the world.</span>

</div>
</div>

